## 🎯 What This Agreement Is About

When you buy ParentControl, you're **not buying the source code**. You're buying a **license**—permission to install and use the app on a specific number of devices.

Think of it like this:
- 🎬 You buy a movie ticket → you can watch the movie, but you don't own the film
- 🏠 You rent an apartment → you can live there, but you don't own the building
- 📱 You buy ParentControl → you can use it, but you don't own the software

---

## ✅ What You CAN Do

With your license, you have the right to:

| ✓ | You Can... |
|---|-----------|
| 📱 | **Install** on the number of devices your license covers |
| 🔧 | **Use** all features for your licensed purpose |
| 🆘 | **Get support** via email and Telegram |
| ⬆️ | **Receive updates** for the duration of your support period |
| 📊 | **Access** the web dashboard and Telegram bot |
| 🔒 | **Keep the app** even if we discontinue it |

---

## ❌ What You CANNOT Do

| ✗ | You Cannot... |
|---|---|
| 🔗 | **Share** copies with other people |
| 💰 | **Resell** or redistribute the software |
| 🔓 | **Reverse engineer** or try to extract the source code |
| 📝 | **Modify** the app or claim you created it |
| 📢 | **Remove** copyright or trademark notices |
| 🚫 | **Use** for illegal surveillance or hacking |
| 🌐 | **Republish** on app stores or websites |

